66
00:04:18,338 --> 00:04:21,471
then to get out, wait for a train,
buy another ticket,

67
00:04:21,471 --> 00:04:23,979
and use the credit card for your bike?

68
00:04:23,979 --> 00:04:26,610
Ideally, you would like
to have one ticket.

69
00:04:26,610 --> 00:04:30,051
Ideally, you would have
to have everything nicely--

70
00:04:30,051 --> 00:04:34,238
all the different modes
nicely interconnected,

71
00:04:34,238 --> 00:04:37,561
and that will make
your urban public transport system

72
00:04:37,561 --> 00:04:40,887
much more attractive vis-Ă -vis the car.

73
00:04:40,887 --> 00:04:44,225
If you have to take the car
before you can take the bus,

74
00:04:44,225 --> 00:04:46,451
and before you can take the train,

75
00:04:46,451 --> 00:04:49,676
then that is not
a really attractive system,

76
00:04:49,676 --> 00:04:51,922
because probably you will have a problem

77
00:04:51,922 --> 00:04:54,708
finding a parking space somewhere.

78
00:04:54,708 --> 00:04:57,769
And the fourth criterion here
is convenience,

79
00:04:57,769 --> 00:05:00,885
