80
00:05:00,885 --> 00:05:04,482
Is the train clean? Is there A/C?

81
00:05:05,171 --> 00:05:09,541
Are you harassed?
Is the bus driver friendly?

82
00:05:09,902 --> 00:05:10,937
These kind of things.

83
00:05:10,937 --> 00:05:14,635
So basically two things
that are important here:

84
00:05:14,635 --> 00:05:18,783
you want the urban
transportation system to be efficient--

85
00:05:18,783 --> 00:05:22,450
in cost, time, and energy terms,

86
00:05:22,450 --> 00:05:25,174
and you want it to be attractive.

87
00:05:25,780 --> 00:05:30,683
And the management
of the urban transportation system,

88
00:05:30,683 --> 00:05:36,132
how it is managed, will decide
how well-performing it is,

89
00:05:36,132 --> 00:05:40,673
how attractive it is,
how efficient it ultimately is.

90
00:05:41,103 --> 00:05:43,929
So the management is the function by which

91
00:05:43,929 --> 00:05:48,649
attractiveness and efficiency
